law.text:
The Oversight Board shall have the following powers and duties:


To advise the Board of County Commissioners regarding compliance by the Miami-Dade County Public Housing Agency, the Miami-Dade County Department of Housing and Community Development and other County departments that administer housing programs with the Fair Housing Act and other housing-related civil rights laws, regulations, ordinances and the County's antidiscrimination policies;



To provide advice to the Board of County Commissioners, the Mayor and the County Manager regarding housing discrimination issues in Miami-Dade County;



To approve and provide a report annually to the Board of County Commissioners regarding compliance of the Miami-Dade Public Housing Agency, the Miami-Dade County Department of Housing and Community Development, and other County departments that administer housing programs with the Fair Housing Act and other housing-related civil rights laws, regulations, ordinances and the County's antidiscrimination policies.
